sentence: Home Depot Inc ( HD ) stock has been upgraded by analysts at Nomura.

But, the conditions that have made HD so attractive are still in

 place - a slow growth economy where home sales remain low, and new

 homes and offices continue to be built while cash is cheap.
Nomura upgraded Home Depot from a "Neutral" to a "Buy" rating on Thursday.
The financial holding company also announced a new price target of $155 for the stock, which is a $15 increase over its previous price target.
Nomura noted that there are signs for growth at Home Depot due to the market is serves and its management team being strong.
It also noted that the company doesn't have to worry about online sales taking away from its business due to customers often needing help with their purchases, reports TheStreet.com.
Home Depot announced during its Q1 earnings report released on May 17 that it's expecting earnings per share for 2016 to be $6.27 .
This is slightly below the $6.31 estimated by Wall Street.
HD shares were up slightly as of Noon Thursday.
